thread.title: U.S. Government Bonds Fall After Jobs Burst

author: Daniel Kruger
title: U.S. Government Bonds Fall After Jobs Burst

organizations.name: u.s. government bonds fall after jobs burst u.s. government

text:
U.S. government bond prices declined Friday after a better-than-expected jobs report signaled the economic outlook remains strong.
The yield on the benchmark 10-year Treasury note rose to 2.894% from 2.866% Thursday, the biggest one-day increase in one week. Yields rise as bond prices fall.
